<br>
First of all, to the guy who implied that myself being able to summon modrods leaves 1/2 the team at the aiport...<br>
<br>
Hmm. First of all, I know of NO raiding guild that doesn't ENCOURAGE max participation, even when your class doesn't stack well with others. Frankly, the more people you have, the quicker kills go, the more margin for error you have, the harder stuff you can kill.<br>
<br>
&lt; I &gt; as a mage didn't eliminate people. As modrods have come in to the game, encounters have gotten HARDER, therefore MORE people are needed.<br>
<br>
As for us as a damage slot on raids -- I don't think we'd ever be as viable as say a monk or rogue on raids. Not saying we can't do damage, however, we don't (esp on raid mobs) do the kind of damage that the other classes in that spot fill. There is NOTHING wrong with us being a damage class, however, some of us define 'usefullness' as having our unique roll on raids. Whether its being a vending machine, or a CoH bisch, or whatever, it is OUR role.<br>
<br>
Finally, define 'overpowered'. Though <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  godrods <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  as they have been affectionately coined by some people are powerful, in light of mob abilities and other spells (manaburn, DC, CH..) they aren't neccesarily 'overpowered'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>Draogan
<BR>
58th Conjurer
