</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvalaglar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valaglar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 7:20:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=328.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages, selfish? (aka a_dead_horse00)</span><hr size=1> I am comfortably into the midhigh-levels, but I have been on plenty of raids (even a Vox raid, which ended up with me being personally clawed by Vox <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Anyway, there is a stark difference between regular solo/xp groups and raids.  Raids are pretty boring for everyone.  Warriors tap their bash and kicks and disciplines, Clerics become CH machines, Wizards sit on their hands half the fight then nuke away, Rogues and Rangers fight like mad then try to avoid getting killed, Necros and Shaman dot, Enchanters drain mana, Mages do rods or nuke, Monks fight and feign.  The point is, in a raid everyone has pretty much one thing they do and it is something that defines them.  Nobody likes it, but then raids are not about xp they are about loot.<br>
<br>
None of us knew what our classes would be like in the high levels (how could we?).  We have to adjust many times as we level up.  Level 34 was a revelation to me as a Mage, when all of a sudden my soloing ability went through the roof.  I can't comment on the high levels, but I know that raids are different and have never been the focus.  We are a powerful class, the new stuff making us more versatile and powerful then ever before.<br>
